@TITLE "Electrics Installation"

@{fg background}@{bg text} Installation @{fg text}@{bg background}

Although Electrics may be run from a floppy disk (a backup copy of the
original disk), it is recommended to install it onto a hard disk.
About 580KB of free disk space is required.

To begin the installation, run the @{" Install " LINK Picture_Database/install.0/MAIN} program.  The default path
to the destination Drawer is "Work:Electrics", and will be created if
it does not already exist.  The destination Drawer may be changed when
installing in "novice user" or "expert user" modes.

@{fg background}@{bg text} Installation Details @{fg text}@{bg background}

During installation, the library "reqtools.library" will be copied to
the "LIBS:" system directory, but only it is not present, or the one
that is present is an older version.  No other files will be copied
to any system directory, nor will any changes will be made the
user-startup file.
@ENDNODE
